    <div class=3D"wpd-comment-text">
    <p>It=E2=80=99s really a question of getting used to it. If you feel co=
mfortable at you current sensitivity and you feel like you=E2=80=99re hitti=
ng all of your shots then there=E2=80=99s no real need to switch, but the r=
eason all pros play at a =E2=80=98lower=E2=80=99 (at least when compared to=
 what many players who are more casual use) sensitivities is because it all=
ows them to have much more control over their micro movements. That said: a=
side from getting a mousepad that=E2=80=99s big enough to accommodate a low=
er sens (you=E2=80=99ll find that all pads that pros use are much larger th=
an what you find on an average office desk, for example) it=E2=80=99s just =
a matter of getting used to it. After a while it starts to feel more natura=
l.<br>
Some people are fans of gradually lowering your sensitivity, which is somet=
hing that you can try if you want, but I am personally more partial to the =
=E2=80=98cold turkey=E2=80=99 method where you just lower it in one go. Tha=
t way you don=E2=80=99t have to get used to a myriad of different sensitivi=
ties. </p>
<p>Hope this helps a bit!</p>

