    <div class=3D"wpd-comment-text">
    <p>It depends. For some 2D games it could make a difference but rotatio=
n in 3D games is usually based on angles, not pixels, so the game doesn=E2=
=80=99t really care about your resolution. That=E2=80=99s why CS:GO pros do=
n=E2=80=99t have to change their sensitivity when they change resolution, f=
or example. If you want to be absolutely sure you can always measure your c=
m/360 though. As far as the infographic goes: that was definitely the avera=
ge sensitivity of players at that time. Our list and guides have been updat=
ed since last week, but even if we look at the median eDPI we can see that =
it=E2=80=99s on the =E2=80=98lower=E2=80=99 side at 251.</p>

